# Contributing to This Project

Thank you for your interest in contributing! Please read these guidelines to ensure your contribution is accepted quickly and clearly.

## Code of Conduct

- Be polite and professional.
- Respect the opinions of others.
- No spam, trolling, or offensive content.

## How to Contribute

1. Fork this repository.
2. Clone your fork:

$ git clone https://github.com/neuxdotdev/rawssg-templates.git

3. Create a new branch:

$ git checkout -b feature/feature-name-or-fix/fixname

4. Make changes and commit:

$ git add .
$ git commit -m "Short description of changes"

5. Push the branch to your fork:

$ git push origin branch-name

6. Open a Pull Request from your fork to the main repository.

## Code Standards

- Use 2-space indentation.
- Use clear and consistent variable naming.
- Follow the project's programming style.
- Include comments if the code is complex or not immediately obvious.

## Git Workflow

- Pull requests must come from the feature/fix branch.
- Commits should be descriptive, clear, and concise.
- Always sync your branch with main before creating a PR.

## Testing

- Ensure all unit tests pass before submitting a PR.
- Add new tests when adding features.
- Use the applicable testing framework for the project.

## Reporting Bugs

- Use [Issues](https://github.com/neuxdotdev/rawssg-templates/issues) to report bugs.
- Include reproduction steps, environment, and error logs if applicable.

## Feature Requests

- Use [Issues](https://github.com/neuxdotdev/rawssg-templates/issues) to request new features.
- Describe the feature's benefits and use cases.

Thank you for your contribution! Every PR or issue will be reviewed, and feedback will be provided as quickly as possible.
